<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: N64 Upgraded Expansion Pak]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12517&amp;p=143425#p143425"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Can the N64 somehow swap out textures while everything is being rendered, but still having the older textures present?<br /></div>Exactly. It can take an arbitrary and widely-varying amount of time to draw a single polygon (even if flat shaded), so you don't have the same kind of &quot;display X sprites every frame&quot; that previous generation hardware had ... and you also don't have the requirement that you finish in 1/60th of a second. Instead, you tell the GPU to draw a triangle ... or a bunch of triangles ... with a bunch of properties.<br /><br />I know nothing about the N64 3d programming interface, but I'd randomly guess it looks like IRIS GL.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Thu Mar 19, 2015 6:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
